Creates a circle Kind: global class See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circumference https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Area https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pi https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radius https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diameter Circle new Circle(options) .pi ⇒ number

Creates a circle Returns: Object - All Measurements Param Type Description options Object [options.radius] number The radius of the circle [options.diameter] number The diameter of the circle [options.circumference] number The circumference of the circle [options.area] number The area of the circle Example (Example 1 - Create Circle by Radius) // returns { radius: 1, diameter: 2, circumference: 3.14, area: 3.14 } new Circle({ radius: 1 }) Example (Example 2 - Create Circle by Diameter) // returns { radius: 1, diameter: 2, circumference: 3.14, area: 3.14 } new Circle({ diameter: 2 }) Example (Example 3 - Create Circle by Circumference) // returns { radius: 1, diameter: 2, circumference: 3.14, area: 3.14 } new Circle({ circumference: 3.14 }) Example (Example 4 - Create Circle by Area) // returns { radius: 1, diameter: 2, circumference: 3.14, area: 3.14 } new Circle({ area: 3.14 })
Gets the value of pi Kind: instance property of Circle See: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pi Example (Example - Get Pi) // returns 3.14 Circle.pi

Creates a Fraction. Kind: global class Fraction new Fraction(numerator, denominator) .simplified() ⇒ Array.<number> .decimal() ⇒ number .percentage() ⇒ number .toString() ⇒ string .toSimplifiedString() ⇒ string

Creates the fraction Param Type Description numerator number The numerator(upper number) of the fraction denominator number The denominator(lower number) of the fraction Example (Example - Create Fraction) // returns { numerator: 3, denominator: 6 } new Fraction(3,6)

Simplify the number Kind: instance method of Fraction Returns: Array.<number> - Simplified Fraction Example (Example - Simplify Fraction) // Returns [1,2] const myFraction = new Fraction(3,6) myFraction.simplified()

Converts the fraction to a decimal Kind: instance method of Fraction Returns: number - Decimal Example (Example - Convert Fraction to Decimal) // returns 0.5 const myFraction = new Fraction(3,6) myFraction.decimal()

Converts the fraction to a percentage Kind: instance method of Fraction Returns: number - Percentage Example (Example - Convert Fraction to Percentage) // returns 50 const myFraction = new Fraction(3,6) myFraction.percentage()

Converts the fraction to a string Kind: instance method of Fraction Returns: string - Fraction String Example (Example - Convert Fraction to String) // returns "3/6" const myFraction = new Fraction(3,6) myFraction.toString()

Converts the fraction to a simplified string Kind: instance method of Fraction Returns: string - Simplified Fraction String Example (Example - Convert Fraction Simplified String) // returns "1/2" const myFraction = new Fraction(3,6) myFraction.toSimplifiedString()
